###Block: Elf Paragon
# Ability Name												Category of Ability		Type					Special ABility		Source Page
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	KEY:Weapon and Armor Proficiency ~ Elf Paragon		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.36	DESC:Elf paragons are proficient with all simple weapons, rapiers, longswords, shortbows, and longbows. Elf paragons are proficient with light armor, but not with shields.		AUTO:WEAPONPROF|TYPE=Simple	AUTO:ARMORPROF|ARMORTYPE=Light
Elfsight				KEY:Elfsight ~ Elf Paragon					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.36	DESC:An elf paragon has exceptional visual acuity. Her racial bonus on Search and Spot checks increases to +4. In addition, an elf paragon's low-light vision increases in range, allowing her to see three times as far as a human in starlight, moonlight, torchlight, and similar conditions of poor illumination.	BONUS:VAR|LowLightDistance|1	BONUS:VAR|ElfSkillBonus|2
Resist Enchantments		KEY:Resist Enchantments ~ Elf Paragon			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.36	DESC:An elf paragon's racial bonus on saves against enchantment spells or effects increases by 2.	BONUS:VAR|ElfSaveBonus|2
Weapon Focus			KEY:Weapon Focus ~ Elf Paragon				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.36	DESC:At 2nd level, an elf paragon gains Weapon Focus as a bonus feat. This feat must apply to either the rapier, longsword, shortsword, shortbow, longbow, composite shortbow, or composite longbow.	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Elf Paragon Weapon Choice|1
Ability Boost			KEY:Ability Boost ~ Elf Paragon				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.36	DESC:At 3rd level, an elf paragon's Intelligence score increases by 2 points		BONUS:STAT|INT|2|TYPE=Racial.STACK
Spells per Day			KEY:Spells ~ Elf Paragon					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.36	DESC:At 2nd and 3rd level, an elf paragon gains new spells per day as if she had also gained a level in wizard. She does not, however, gain any other benefi t a character of that class would have gained (bonus metamagic feats, and so on). This essentially means that she adds the level of elf paragon to her level in wizard, then determines spells per day and caster level accordingly. If an elf paragon has no levels in wizard, this class feature has no effect.

###Block: Gnome Paragon
# Ability Name			Output Name			Category of Ability		Type					Special ABility			Innate Spells										Caster level								Bonus to skill							Source Page
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	KEY:Weapon and Armor Proficiency ~ Gnome Paragon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality			DESC:Gnome paragons are proficient with all simple weapons and with light armor.		AUTO:WEAPONPROF|TYPE=Simple	AUTO:ARMORPROF|ARMORTYPE=Light
Illusion Aptitude			KEY:Illusion Aptitude ~ Gnome Paragon			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:A gnome paragon may add his class level to his caster level to determine the effects of any illusion spells he casts, including those gained as innate abilities of the gnome race. This bonus stacks with the extra spellcasting levels gained from the gnome paragon's spells per day entry (see above). For example, a 2nd-level wizard/3rd-level gnome paragon's caster level is 2nd for most wizard spells but 5th for wizard spells of the illusion school (and 4th for his innate spell-like abilities dancing lights, ghost sound, and prestidigitation). A 3rd-level bard/2nd-level gnome paragon's caster level is 5th for most bard spells but 7th for bard spells of the illusion school. This increased caster level affects only spells that the character can cast; it does not give him access to higher-level spells or more spells per day.													BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SCHOOL.Illusion|var("CL=Gnome Paragon")										SOURCEPAGE:p.37
Keen Senses				KEY:Keen Senses ~ Gnome Paragon				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:A gnome paragon's racial bonus on Listen checks and Craft (alchemy) checks increases to +4.																								BONUS:SKILL|Listen,Craft (Alchemy)|4|TYPE=Racial	SOURCEPAGE:p.37
Gnome Paragon Mirror Image	KEY:Mirror Image ~ Gnome Paragon				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.SpellLike		DESC:At 2nd level, a gnome paragon gains the ability to cast mirror image once per day as a spell-like ability with a caster level equal to his gnome paragon level.	SPELLS:Innate|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=var("CL=Gnome Paragon")|Mirror Image																				SOURCEPAGE:p.37
Spells per Day			KEY:Spells ~ Gnome Paragon					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality			DESC:At 2nd and 3rd level, a gnome paragon gains new spells per day and spells known as if he had also gained a level in bard. He does not, however, gain any other benefit a character of that class would have gained (bard class features, and so on). This essentially means that he adds the level of gnome paragon to his level in bard, then determines spells per day, spells known, and caster level accordingly.
Ability Boost			KEY:Ability Boost ~ Gnome Paragon				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:At 3rd level, a gnome paragon's Charisma score increases by 2 points.	BONUS:STAT|CHA|2|TYPE=Racial.STACK


